Title : Malaysian Global Innovation and Creativity Centre
Text : The '''Malaysian Global Innovation and Creativity Centre''' or '''MaGIC''' is an innovation and creativity centre located at [[Persiaran APEC]], [[Cyberjaya]], [[Selangor]], [[Malaysia]]. The centre which is under the [[Ministry of Finance (Malaysia)|Ministry of Finance]] was officially opened on 27 April 2014, by the [[Malaysian Prime Minister]], [[Najib Tun Razak]] and his counterpart [[US President]], [[Barack Obama]] in conjunction of his visit to the country from 26 to 28 April 2014.

[[Cheryl Yeoh]] was appointed as the first and founding CEO of MaGIC on 15 April 2014<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.themalaymailonline.com/tech-gadgets/article/ceo-cheryl-yeoh-lays-out-magics-ingredients|title=CEO Cheryl Yeoh Lays Out MaGIC's Ingredients|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Malay Mail|access-date=}}</ref> and ended her contract on 14 January 2016.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.techinasia.com/cheryl-yeoh-magic-legacy|title=Cheryl Yeoh MaGIC Legacy|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Tech in Asia|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://e27.co/whatever-work-future-will-global-impact-magic-ceo-cheryl-yeoh-20151214/|title=Whatever I Work On In The Future Will Have a Global Impact: Cheryl Yeoh|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=e27|access-date=}}</ref>

The '''Obama Oval''' at the building compound was named after [[US President]], [[Barack Obama]].

Key MaGIC employees have gone on to start startups such as [[Amazing Fables]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://player.fm/series/series-1497798/storytime-with-amazing-fables|title=Storytime With Amazing Fables BFM :: Open For Business podcast|last=FM|first=Player|website=player.fm|language=en|access-date=2019-01-27}}</ref> and GoCar<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bfm.my/bg-alan-cheah-gocar-can-gocar-go-the-distance.html|title=BFM: The Business Radio Station - Can GoCar Go The Distance?|website=www.bfm.my|access-date=2019-01-27}}</ref>.

